org.foxlabs.validation.constraint

Class UrlAddressConstraint

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.foxlabs.validation.AbstractValidation<V>
      • org.foxlabs.validation.constraint.CheckConstraint<String>
        • org.foxlabs.validation.constraint.UrlAddressConstraint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Constraint<String>, Validation<String>

    public final class UrlAddressConstraint
extends CheckConstraint<String>
    This class provides CheckConstraint implementation that checks whether a string is valid URL reference. Also the allowed set of protocols and prefix pattern can be configured. Note that prefix should not describe URL protocol. For example, prefix of the SCM URL scm:svn:http://svn.foxlabs.org should be defined as scm:svn: or scm:[a-z]: regex.
    Author:
    Fox Mulder
    See Also:
    UrlAddress, ConstraintFactory.urlAddress(), ConstraintFactory.urlAddress(String, String...)
